Nick Giannopoulos https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nick_Giannopoulos 0 Nicholas "Nick" Giannopoulos (Greek: Νικόλαος "Νίκος" Γιαννόπουλος; born 1 July 1963 in Melbourne, Australia) is an Australian stand-up comedian, film and TV actor and film director of Greek descent. He is best known for his comedy stage show Wogs Out of Work alongside George Kapiniaris, the television sitcom Acropolis Now and the film The Wog Boy and has been described as "Australia's leading exponent of "wog" humour".
